<li>Haynes, Roslynn Doris (1994). <i>From Faust to Strangelove: Representations of the Scientist in Western Literature</i>. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0801848016" class="internal">ISBN 0-8018-4801-6</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Christopher_Frayling" title="Christopher Frayling">Christopher Frayling</a> – <i>Mad, Bad and Dangerous?: The Scientist and the Cinema</i> (Reaktion Books, 2005) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1861892551" class="internal">ISBN 1-86189-255-1</a></li>
<li>Junge, Torsten; Doerthe Ohlhoff (2004). <i>Wahnsinnig genial: Der Mad Scientist Reader. Aschaffenburg: Alibri. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/3932710797" class="internal">ISBN 3-932710-79-7</a>.</i></li>
